'''Playa de Gulpiyuri''' is a flooded [[sinkhole]]<ref name="vivirasturias">{{cite web | url=http://www.vivirasturias.com/asturias/llanes/playa-de-gulpiyuri/es | title=Gulpiyuri beach | accessdate=June 10, 2012 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618201903/http://www.vivirasturias.com/asturias/llanes/playa-de-gulpiyuri/es | archivedate=June 18, 2012 | df= }}</ref> with an inland beach located near [[Llanes]], in Asturias  Northern Spain, around 100 m from the [[Cantabrian Sea]].<ref name="acampamos">{{cite web | url=http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&prev=/search%3Fq%3DPlaya%2Bde%2BGulpiyuri%26hl%3Den%26safe%3Dactive%26prmd%3Dimvns&rurl=translate.google.com&sl=es&u=http://www.acampamos.com/comunidades/asturias/turismo/costas_y_playas/playa_de_gulpiyuri/playa_de_gulpiyuri.htm&usg=ALkJrhguM5ccs0bJSDNmrY7OERujjzvGDA | title=Gulpiyuri beach: Beaches and Coasts of Asturias | publisher=acampamos.com | accessdate=June 10, 2012}}</ref> Roughly 40 meters in length, it is fully tidal due to a series of underground tunnels carved by the [[seawater|salt water]] of the Cantabrian Sea which allows water from the [[Bay of Biscay]] to create small waves.<ref name="Oddities">{{cite web | url=http://www.odditycentral.com/pics/playa-de-gulpiyuri-a-strange-beach-in-the-middle-of-a-meadow.html | title=Playa de Gulpiyuri – A Strange Beach in the Middle of a Meadow | accessdate=June 10, 2012}}</ref>  

It is a popular tourist destination, [[natural monument]], and part of Spain's Regional Network of Protected Natural Areas.<ref name="vivirasturias" /><ref name="acampamos" />

